HEADWORD: Woundwort
<hw>Wound"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any one of certain plants whose soft, downy leaves have been used
for dressing wounds, as the kidney vetch, and several species of the
labiate genus <gen>Stachys</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woundy</ent>⟦br⟧
